<P>
KARIYA HAS GOAL AND ASSIST IN DEBUT FOR DUCKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROBYN NORWOOD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Mighty Ducks lost to the Dallas Stars, 4-3, in an exhibition game Tuesday 
at Reunion Arena that marked the debut of rookie Paul Kariya. 
</P>
<P>
 Kariya, 19, had a goal and an assist, both in the third period, and rookie 
linemate Valeri Karpov, 23, also had a goal and an assist.The two young wingers 
are playing on a line with veteran center Anatoli Semenov, 32. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was a learning experience," Kariya said. "I have to learn what I can and 
can't do at this level. Nothing comes just like that. It takes years, not just 
one game." 
</P>
<P>
 Kariya's goal, at 15:20 of the third, came on what he called "a bad pass" 
meant for Semenov. Instead, the puck went in off defenseman Craig Ludwig. 
</P>
<P>
 The game also marked the debut of veteran defenseman Tom Kurvers, a power-play 
specialist the Ducks traded for during the off-season. Kurvers scored the 
Ducks' first goal -- on a power play -- at 12:46 of the second. ROBYN NORWOOD 
