<P>
FISH REPORT: ANGLER DOESN'T GIVE UP, LANDS A LUNKER CATFISH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Henry Yee got mad, but then he got even. Sort of. 
</P>
<P>
 Fishing for catfish at Irvine Lake on a recent morning, he took his eye off 
his pole and it was promptly pulled overboard by what was believed to be a 
large catfish. 
</P>
<P>
 Yee went home for another rod, went back to the same location at the lake, and 
pulled out a 24-pound channel catfish.  
</P>
<P>
 Catfish angling remains superb at the lake, with several fish tipping the 
scales at more than 10 pounds. 
</P>
