<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETE OF THE WEEK / GIRLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Amy Skieresz 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: Agoura 
</P>
<P>
 SPORT: Cross-country 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Senior 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: Skieresz, 1993 State Division I cross-country champion, 
sat out her junior track season to raise her grades to her parents' standards. 
The layoff does not appear to have hurt.On Saturday, she opened the season with 
a runaway victory in the senior race of the Seaside Invitational at San 
Buenaventura State Beach in Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 WEEK AT A GLANCE: Skieresz won by 59 seconds and her time of 17 minutes 21 
seconds over the three-mile distance moved her to fourth on the all-time course 
list. "I hadn't raced in so long so I just wanted to get out there and see how 
it felt," Skieresz said. "I really had no expectations at all about times." 
</P>
