ATHLETE OF THE WEEK / BOYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ted Iacenda 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: Hart 
</P>
<P>
 SPORT: Football 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Junior 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: As a sophomore last year, Iacenda scored 20 touchdowns. 
He's well on his way to topping that total with five touchdowns in the 1994 
opener last week. 
</P>
<P>
 WEEK AT A GLANCE: The 6-foot-1, 205-pound running back rushed for 120 yards in 
nine carries and caught four passes for 74. He had touchdown runs of 12, 6, 47 
and 3 yards. He also took a shovel pass from quarterback Steve McKeon 19 yards 
for a score. Each time, Iacenda raced through the line of scrimmage untouched, 
then either ran over or around defenders in the secondary. "What can I say?" he 
said. "It's fun to run on defensive backs." 
</P>
