WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; GRAND JURY INDICTS MAN IN JULY SLAYING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Ventura County Grand Jury has indicted a 23-year-old gang member accused 
of fatally shooting another gang member over a romantic triangle, prosecutors 
said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Thomas Al Corral, 23, is scheduled to be arraigned in Ventura County Superior 
Court today on a charge of murder.He also faces a kidnaping charge from an 
unrelated 1991 case. 
</P>
<P>
 Prosecutors say Corral burst through the door of his ex-girlfriend's Ventura 
home July 21 and shot Roger Rowland, 23. 
</P>
<P>
 By obtaining the indictment through the grand jury, prosecutors avoid having 
to prove that there is sufficient evidence to hold Corral on the charges at a 
preliminary hearing. 
</P>
<P>
 Corral and a co-defendant, Ruben Viveros, were arrested in Las Vegas a week 
after Rowland's death.  
</P>
<P>
 Viveros, who is charged with accessory to murder, is being held at the Ventura 
County Jail in lieu of $250,000 bail. 
</P>
<P>
 Because of an outstanding arrest warrant from a 1991 case, Corral is being 
held without bail, authorities said. DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
</TEXT>
