<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY EDITION: DOCENTS SOUGHT FOR HISTORICAL PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Simi Valley Historical Society is looking for residents with a strong 
interest in history, a healthy dose of patience and plenty of free time to 
volunteer as docents at the Strathearn Historical Park. 
</P>
<P>
 The park, situated off Madera Road, is a popular city landmark that showcases 
the artifacts and old homes of the city's founding families and the Native 
Americans who lived here before them. 
</P>
<P>
 Tours are given year-round, but extra volunteer guides are needed during the 
school year when large groups of children visit the park. 
</P>
<P>
 Docents will undergo 12 hours of training over three days and will begin 
leading students on hourlong tours in early October, docent Seree Schnepf said. 
</P>
<P>
 Of the 10 positions available, two have been filled. For more information, 
call Schnepf at 583-1956. MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</TEXT>
