<HEADLINE>
<P>
TREATMENT NEEDED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Regarding the Aug. 16 article on the arrest of a 29-year-old male from 
Fillmore: It took 50 law enforcement officers. Have we taxpayers no say in this 
craziness? 
</P>
<P>
 This young man has repeatedly gone to jail for alcohol-related crimes. Did it 
ever occur to the district attorney and judge that this man should be treated 
at a recovery center with follow up for at least one year? We must recognize 
alcoholism as an illness. It is serious and endangering to others. 
</P>
<P>
 By providing more treatment centers, focusing on employment after release and 
living conditions, maybe we could help. By jailing these individuals we do not 
improve them; we further provide no hope. 
</P>
<P>
 Why can't we utilize our tax dollars to better advantage? Shame on our system. 
Our fellow human beings deserve better. 
</P>
