<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY EDITION: SIMI VALLEY; DISABLED OFFERED VAN SERVICE ON 
SATURDAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Simi Valley Transit has extended its curb-to-curb van service for disabled 
riders to include Saturdays. 
</P>
<P>
 As with weekday service, vans on Saturdays will be provided from 8 a.m. to 
4:30 p.m. for trips within the city limits. Bus fares are $1 and transportation 
requests must be made at least one day in advance. 
</P>
<P>
 Saturday service is required under the federal Americans with Disabilities 
Act, and is provided in conjunction with Simi Valley Transit's Dial-A-Ride 
service. 
</P>
<P>
 "People who cannot ride the regular buses are entitled to a more compatible 
service," management analyst Hibbie Hayslett explained. "It is to take the 
place of a fixed-route bus."  
</P>
<P>
 Transportation requests may be made by calling 583-6464. TRACY WILSON 
</P>
