COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: COSTA MESA; ORANGE COAST TO OFFER ADOPTION WORKSHOP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A workshop designed for persons interested in child adoption is being offered 
by the Orange Coast College community services office. 
</P>
<P>
 The non-credit class, entitled "Adoption Option," is scheduled for 9 a.m. to 
noon Sept. 24 in the Lewis Applied Science Building. 
</P>
<P>
 The instructors are Nancy Miller Salzman, an attorney and adoptive mother, and 
Elizabeth Knego, a licensed clinical social worker. Among the topics explored 
will be the pros and cons of various adoption choices, short- and long-term 
ramifications, and the legal process. 
</P>
<P>
 The workshop registration fee is $29 for individuals or $45 for couples. 
Orange Coast College is at 2701 Fairview Road. For more information, call (714) 
432-5880. 
