<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: INSURANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Insurance Department to Close Division: The state agency will close its Los 
Angeles-based conservation and liquidation division by year-end, laying off 
about 70 employees, Insurance Commissioner John Garamendi announced.The 
division, which manages the assets of about 60 failed insurers, has been 
criticized for management problems by state auditors. The unit will be 
reorganized and moved to San Francisco, a move that will pare $1 million from 
the division's $17-million annual budget, according to a department 
spokeswoman. Relocating the unit near the Insurance Department's main office 
will "substantially improve oversight, accountability and coordination," 
Garamendi said in a statement. Laid-off employees may apply for jobs in San 
Francisco, the department said. 
</P>
