<TEXT>
<P>
 Caesars to Bid for Indiana Casino: Caesars World Inc. of Los Angeles said it 
will team with privately held Riverboat Development Inc. in a bid to develop a 
casino on the Ohio River in Harrison County, Ind. If the bid is successful, 
Caesars said, it will own 10% of the riverboat gambling hall and will manage 
the facility, while Riverboat Development will hold a 50% ownership stake, with 
the rest held by other investors.No other gaming companies have bid for the new 
project, Caesars said. The application deadline is still about two months away. 
Caesars, Circus Circus Enterprises and Hilton Hotels Corp. are already jointly 
bidding to develop a casino in northern Indiana, about 250 miles from the 
Harrison County site. 
