<HEADLINE>
<P>
AST RESEARCH FACES SHAREHOLDER LAWSUIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Computer maker AST Research Inc., already facing two lawsuits alleging that it 
misled investors early this year, was sued again Tuesday by shareholders who 
said the computer maker duped them about its financial condition this summer. 
</P>
<P>
 The latest class action was filed in U.S. District Court in Los Angeles by the 
same law firm that filed one of the lawsuits in March.It came 12 days after the 
company's stock price dropped nearly $4.94 a share to $13.06 a share after AST 
revealed that it expects to post a large loss, instead of the expected profit, 
for the current quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 AST lawyer Robert Vanderet said the latest lawsuit against the Irvine-based 
technology company "appears to be another knee-jerk abusive securities fraud 
suit of the kind that are routinely filed after the announcement of adverse 
financial news." 
</P>
</TEXT>
