<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Groundwater Remediation Inc.: The Orange County company, which cleans 
contaminated soil and ground water, said Tuesday it is being purchased by an 
environmental holding company based in Hawaii. 
</P>
<P>
 EIF Holdings Inc. of Honolulu said it expects to close the deal by the end of 
the month.Terms were not released. 
</P>
<P>
 EIF Holdings is in an acquisition phase, Executive Vice President Andy 
Kasianchuk said. Groundwater Remediation, based in Orange, was an attractive 
target primarily because it has a presence in California, he said. "It is a 
small company, but through our eight offices in California we will be able to 
market its services." 
</P>
<P>
 Groundwater Remediation, which is also involved with the construction and 
servicing of underground tanks, will continue to provide services in 
California, Nevada and Arizona. 
</P>
