<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: COSTA MESA; CHEERLEADERS REACH U.S. CONTEST FINALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TOM RAGAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Costa Mesa High School varsity cheerleading squad has made it to the 
National Cheerleading Finals in Orlando, Fla. 
</P>
<P>
 The squad, called Spirit Leaders, finished first among 50 high schools from 
across the state in a meet at UCLA last month, sponsored by the United Dance 
Assn. 
</P>
<P>
 Last Friday, the cheerleaders performed the dance that catapulted them into 
the national finals during a pep rally in the high school's main gym. 
</P>
<P>
 There's one obstacle in the way of the competition in Orlando, Fla.: The girls 
must raise $20,000 to pay for the trip. 
</P>
<P>
 "We've got to raise the money by February," said an anxious Lance 
Thompson-Hailstone, whose daughter, Rachel, a junior, is a member of the squad. 
"That means we need a lot of commitment and a lot of help, because it's a lot 
of money in such a short period of time." 
</P>
<P>
 While the cheerleaders are out hawking entertainment booklets that offer 50% 
off at fancy restaurants and fast-food chains around the county, parents are 
trying to contact possible sponsors, said Thompson-Hailstone. 
</P>
<P>
 Carwashes and garage sales will also be held. 
</P>
<P>
 If the girls compete in the finals, it will do wonders for the reputation of 
the high school, parents and teachers say. 
</P>
<P>
 "It will be very prestigious," said Thompson-Hailstone. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call Joanne Shimpock at (714) 556-3192. Contributions 
can be sent to Costa Mesa High School, c/o Spirit Leaders, 2650 Fairview Road, 
Costa Mesa, Calif. 92626. TOM RAGAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
