<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: GARDEN GROVE; NEW BUSINESS HOURS AT POLICE DEPARTMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Police Department has changed the business hours at its headquarters on 
Acacia Parkway, a spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Capt. Dave Abrecht said that under the new schedule, which took effect 
Saturday, non-emergency matters, such as requests for insurance reports, will 
be accepted from 8 a.m. to 6 p.m. Monday through Saturday at the front desk. 
</P>
<P>
 The lobby and front desk are closed for business on Sundays, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 The changes will enable the department to provide better service because all 
desk employees will be available during the designated business hours, Abrecht 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 "Every effort is being made to deploy our limited resources in a manner that 
has the most impact on community safety," he said. "This will allow us to place 
a majority of our . . . personnel in the field, solving neighborhood problems." 
</P>
<P>
 Business hours were previously 7:30 a.m. to 9:30 p.m. daily. The new schedule 
is the result of a recent study that indicated the hours that people are likely 
to conduct non-emergency business, Abrecht said. 
</P>
<P>
 However, members of the public may still make non-emergency police reports by 
telephone between 6 a.m. and 10 p.m. every day, he said. BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</TEXT>
