COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: LOS ALAMITOS; COUNCIL OKS UPDATE OF DEVELOPMENT LAWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council has tentatively approved an ordinance that would set 
guidelines for land development in the city. 
</P>
<P>
 It voted 4 to 0 on Monday to approve a subdivision ordinance updating the 
city's development laws for the first time in more than 20 years. Councilman 
Charles E. Sylvia was absent. 
</P>
<P>
 The ordinance will reflect changes in state law and recent court rulings 
relating to how land is parceled or combined for development, City Atty. Thomas 
W. Allen said. 
</P>
<P>
 A key provision requires developers to notify neighboring property owners 
before dividing or combining lots for housing or commercial development. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition, the ordinance would require developers to set aside areas for 
public uses in proposed developments. BERT ELJERA 
</P>
