<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD GREW BY 1.9 MILLION DURING POPULATION MEETING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In the eight days, eight hours and 45 minutes of the U.N. population 
conference in Cairo, about 3,056,000 babies were born into the world -- an 
average of about four babies every second. 
</P>
<P>
 Over the same period about 1,167,000 people died, leaving a net increase of 
1,889,000 in population. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA091494-0248 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 079116 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
