<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN STABBED IN O.C. SCHOOL PARKING LOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An unidentified man was stabbed with a screwdriver and critically injured 
Tuesday on the grounds of Western High School in the 500 block of South Western 
Street, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The stabbing took place just before 3 p.m. on a school parking lot, according 
to Sgt. Steve Rodig, while the man sat in a car waiting for friends to get out 
of class. 
</P>
<P>
 A second man approached the car and stabbed the victim and then fled. The 
wounded man, who was not a student or faculty member, left the car and ran a 
short distance before collapsing. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses told police the man was stabbed with a screwdriver. 
</P>
<P>
 Paramedics treated the victim at the scene and transported him to UCI Medical 
Center in Orange, where he was reported in critical condition, Rodig said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police have no motive for the attack and have not identified the suspect. 
</P>
</TEXT>
